{
  "title": "GEB (Geographical Environmental and Behavioural model)",
  "description": "GEB simulates the environment (e.g., hydrology, floods), individual people, households, and organizations as well as their interactions at both small and large scale. The model employs a 'deep' coupling of an agent-based model, a hydrological model, a vegetation model, and a hydrodynamic model.",
